330 Pleasant Ave., east side, between 117th and 118th Streets. This building is an old house which has been used for a dozen or more years as a Settlement House (The Neighborhood House), of the Church Extension Committee of the Presbytery of New York and is now being given up. July 13, 1927.

P. L. Sperr.

(2)
The same, five years later.
1932.

J. Clarence Davies Collection, Museum of the City of New York. Negative No. 252.

East 117th Street, west from Pleasant Avenue, showing pavement conditions on the north side of this street. At the left midground is the institutional building that houses P. S. No. 85. This is at the S. W. corner of First Avenue. View 2 shows details of the sidewalk at the N.E. corner at that Avenue. The Second Avenue "El" station appears in the background of both views.

May 4, 1937
No's. 1-2

W. P. A., photo
